               <p>GEORGE MICHAEL BEINDER. I <rs id="t18170416-235-viclabel1247" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18170416-235-crimeloc1248">sign of the City of Norwich, in Wentworth-street, Spitalfields</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-235-crimeloc1248" type="placeName" value="sign of the City of Norwich, in Wentworth-street, Spitalfields"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-235-crimeloc1248" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-235-off1245 t18170416-235-crimeloc1248"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-235-victim1725 t18170416-235-viclabel1247"></join>. On the 4th of April I missed the property from the club-room, up stairs-the prisoner used to sleep in my club-room - He left it on the 17th of April - I had him secured. I found my waistcoat in his portmanteau.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170416-235-person1726">
                  RICHARD 
                  WATLEY
               <interp inst="t18170416-235-person1726" type="surname" value="WATLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-235-person1726" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-235-person1726" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 17th of April I took the prisoner into custody. He said he did not put the waistcoat into his portmanteau. I found duplicates of the property upon him - He then acknowledged taking it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170416-235-person1727">
                  JAMES 
                  HULME
               <interp inst="t18170416-235-person1727" type="surname" value="HULME"></interp>
